## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of sources and the potential bias in the selected articles. The debate on book banning is highly subjective, and perspectives can vary widely based on cultural, social, and individual values. Additionally, the report does not cover all possible arguments or perspectives due to the constraints of the available data and the scope of the research. Further research could include more empirical studies on the impact of book banning on student learning outcomes and psychological effects.